metadata.name: Unicorn #8635
metadata.description:
All of us have dreams, and everyone would like to meet a fairy, a genie, a wizard, or someone else who will make our dreams come true in a snap of a finger or with the wave of a wand. But we're the only ones who can do it. We are those magical unicorns, unique, inimitable, with our own qualities and magical abilities.
These unicorns are the visualization of our inner selves that makes our dreams come true. An embodiment of all the best with a huge positive magical power.

Twitter: @unicorn_nft_art
Web: https://unicorn-nft.web.app/

by @lucky26puch, @AgataBaranova17
Made in 2022

metadata.name: Balanced #163
metadata.description:
What does balance look like when viewed through the lens of pure mathematics? This is the question Balanced attempts to answer.

Each output is composed of a unique collection of blocks mathematically stacked to be in perfect balance.

This is my Genesis project. Enjoy!

Interactions:
1 - Reverse your stack vertically and re-balance.
2 - Toggle between square and portrait frame.
3 - Show center of mass. 
4 - Toggle the border.
5 - Toggle the background (color/transparent)
6 - Export image (2048x2048)
7 - Export image (4096x4096)
8 - Export image (8192x8192)

How it was made: https://www.jeffweber.art/balanced

metadata.name: Multivoid Feedback Powers #10
metadata.description:
Behold the feedback microchip's design,
It transcends the abyss of our mind,
A force of energy that can't be confined,
And colors that are simply unaligned.

A marvel of technology we see,
A chip that unlocks creativity,
A bridge that connects the mind's duality,
With colors that dazzle with vitality.

The feedback microchip, a work of art,
A synergy of science and heart,
An innovation that sets us apart,
With colors that ignite the spark.

So let us embrace this wonder in our midst,
And let our minds and creativity enlist,
With the feedback microchip, there's no resist,
Its energy and colors can't be dismissed.

This one goes for you K. Thanks for making me want to do hydra things. 

Made in HydraSynth by Olivia Jack.

metadata.name: WTBS Logo with Fractals #238
metadata.description:
Hard to believe we are going into month 3 of making the podcast! In February we further honed our sound thanks to new microphones and editing, and released our first two artist interview episodes w/ abstractment and MJLindow. Lots more interviews to come!

Thank you to everyone who takes the time to write us kind messages of support. Extra thanks to everyone who helps to grow the show by sharing/retweeting. Extra extra thanks to everyone who supports us through donations and/or collecting our NFT releases.

This project is coded in p5.js with help from abstractment (master of formatting). It is quite a bit different from the first... hopefully you will enjoy the added complexity and variations. There were quite a few discoveries and happy accidents along the way to make it possible. If you are new to coding or otherwise interested in learning, please feel free to browse the code. Effort has been made to explain, as best as possible, how everything works with comments... although this will assume a bit more knowledge than the last.
